title: H.S. football: Offensive Player of the Year Watch - Football
text:
Offensive Player of the Year watch 
Malik Bakker, Don Bosco, sr. RB 
Rushed 20 times for 101 yards and three TDs in barely more than a half during a victory at Passaic Tech. Has 843 rushing yards and 11 TDs in six games.
Jedh Downey, NV/Old Tappan, sr. TE
Caught three passes for 89 yards and two TDs and rushed for another score in the Golden Knights' win over Pascack Valley. Has 18 receptions for 362 yards and eight TDs in six games.
Peter Guerriero, Lyndhurst, sr. QB 
Produced 331 rushing yards and four TDs on 26 attempts, and threw for 106 yards and a TD in the Golden Bears' loss to Glen Rock. On pace to rush for over 2,300 yards (through six games, 1,394 yards on 132 carries).
Derius Stone, St. Mary, sr. RB
Churned out 233 rushing yards and four TDs on 19 carries in a loss to Hasbrouck Heights. Through six games, has rushed 147 times for 1,323 yards and 21 TDs.
Keith Woetzel, Ramapo, sr. QB 
Threw for 133 yards and three scores and ran 13 times for 195 yards and two TDs to lead the Raiders over Indian Hills. In six games, has passed for 854 yards and nine TDs, in addition to rushing for 526 yards and nine TDs on 57 attempts.
